@startuml
title ArcHub Rust Core Plugin Distribution

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Platform Maintainer" as Maintainer
component "ArcHubPluginRegistry" as Registry
component "KnowledgePluginManifest\ncore=true, runtime=rust" as Manifest
component "Rust Workspace\nCargo.toml" as Workspace
component "Core Crate\nrust/<crate>" as Crate
component "ModuleDistributionBuilder" as Builder
artifact "Marketplace Archive\nplugin.json + Cargo.toml + rust/*" as Archive
database "Marketplace Repository\nmarketplace.json" as Marketplace
component "ModuleDistributionInstaller" as Installer
component "PluginManagementService" as Management
component "Core Coverage API\n/api/platform/core-plugins" as Api

Maintainer --> Registry : build marketplace
Registry --> Manifest : built-in core manifests
Manifest --> Workspace : rust_crate
Workspace --> Crate : resolve crate path
Manifest --> Builder
Crate --> Builder : source files
Builder --> Archive
Builder --> Marketplace : index item\nsha256 + rust metadata
Marketplace --> Installer : selected package
Installer --> Management : installed metadata
Management --> Api : coverage + declaration report

note right of Builder
Core packages include:
- plugin.json
- README.md
- minimal Cargo.toml
- rust/archub-core
- rust/<target-crate>
end note

note bottom of Api
Coverage is valid only when:
missing_total = 0
undeclared_total = 0
end note

@enduml
